<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="550" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1253,1494]" pageId="1" pageNumber="550">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,1253,1278]" pageId="1" pageNumber="550">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Five dc; 
<number box="[380,394,1253,1277]" pageId="1" pageNumber="550" value="4.0">4</number>
very short, paired acr before 
<number box="[730,744,1253,1277]" pageId="1" pageNumber="550" value="1.0">1</number>
dc. Antenna dark brown with dark yellow scape. Fore femur with two rows of weak ventral setae at base. Mid tarsomeres 
<number box="[847,889,1289,1313]" pageId="1" pageNumber="550" value="3.0" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="2.0">2–4</number>
flattened (
<figureCitation box="[1011,1093,1289,1313]" captionStart="FIGURES 11 – 13" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1365,1388]" captionTargetBox="[256,1327,220,1344]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[243,1343,195,1344]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 11 – 13. Mid and hind tarsi, lateral view. 11. Amblypsilopus basalis Yang, mid tarsus; 12. Amblypsilopus basalis Yang, hind tarsus; 13. Amblypsilopus flaviappendiculatus (de Meijere), hind tarsus. Scale bar 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222178/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="550">
Fig. 
<number box="[1064,1093,1289,1313]" pageId="1" pageNumber="550" value="11.0">11</number>
</figureCitation>
). Male cercus long finger-like with thick basal process (
<figureCitation box="[434,503,1325,1349]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 10" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1348,1371]" captionTargetBox="[188,1428,370,1317]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,341,1337]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 10. Male genitalia, lateral view. 8. Amblypsilopus basalis Yang; 9. Amplypsilopus capitatus Yang; 10. Amblypsilopus flaviappendiculatus (de Meijere). Scale bar 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222177/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="550">
